{{Aimai}}

{{字引|date=2017年11月}}
'''Umedo''' (埋土) refers to:

* A general term for soil used to fill holes or depressions in the ground.
* A term mainly used in {{ill|archaeology|ja|考古学}} to describe the soil deposited within {{ill|archaeological features|ja|遺構}}. It is also referred to as {{ill|fukudo (archaeology)|ja|覆土 (考古学)}}. In {{ill|archaeology|ja|考古学}} and {{ill|excavation surveys|ja|発掘調査}}, the two terms are used almost synonymously. For example, in the reference literature listed below, it is described as "埋土（覆土）".{{Sfn|Agency for Cultural Affairs|2010|pp=94}}

== Notes ==
{{脚注ヘルプ}}
{{Reflist}}

== References ==
* {{Cite book|language=ja|ref=harv|author=Agency for Cultural Affairs|authorlink=Agency for Cultural Affairs|chapter=Chapter IV: Recognition of Soil Layers and Excavation of Surface and Inclusion Layers|title=Excavation Survey Guide: Settlement Site Excavation Edition|pages=93-116|date=2010-05|year=2010|publisher={{ill|Dōsei Publishing|ja|同成社}}|isbn=9784886215253}}

[[Category:Archaeology]]
{{Ambiguity}}
[[ja:埋土]]

