* A general term for soil used to fill holes or depressions in the ground. * A term mainly used in {{ill|archaeology|ja|考古学}} to describe the soil deposited within {{ill|archaeological features|ja|遺構}}. It is also referred to as {{ill|fukudo (archaeology)|ja|覆土 (考古学)|1=Overburden (archaeology)|lt=Overburden}}. In {{ill|archaeology|ja|考古学}} and {{ill|excavation surveys|ja|発掘調査}}, the two terms are used almost synonymously. For example, in the reference literature listed below, it is described as "埋土（覆土）".{{Sfn|Agency for Cultural Affairs|2010|pp=94}}
